# VRM upload — protected (do not regress)

**User-confirmed good state (2026-06-18).** Read `memory-bank/vrm-upload-protected-state.md` and `docs/VRM_UPLOAD_DISPLAY_EXPORT.md` before editing upload/display/export paths.

## Invariants

| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| Upload | `passthrough: true` → scene-root yaw only if needed; **no** scale, rebind, rename, AIGC repair |
| Flags | `userData.vrmBindPassthrough` + `userData.vrmNormalized` on uploaded VRM |
| Display | Skip `processModel` / `normalizeRiggedModelTransforms` repair for passthrough VRM |
| Skeleton | Fixed `SKELETON_JOINT_SPHERE_RADIUS` (0.012); uniform; overlay `depthTest: false` |
| Export | No blind π yaw; no rebind that breaks passthrough bind |

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- Wiring **image-to-avatar**, **avatar-from-image**, or **`fromAigc`** rig fixes into VRM upload/load paths.
- Shared debug changes in `sceneManager.js`, `rigBoneUtils.js`, `vrmLoader.js` that lack `vrm` / `vrmBindPassthrough` guards.
- Re-enabling hips-only rotation or per-skin rebind on multi-skin VRM0 uploads.

## Protected files

`vrmLoader.js`, `sceneManager.js`, `rigBoneUtils.js`, `VRMExporter.js`, `characterManager.js`, `vrmManager.js`, `load-utils.js`, `modelOrientationUtils.js`

## Before merging touches to protected files

Re-test multi-skin VRM0 upload + skeleton mode + export round-trip. Grep remote log for `[VRM] Upload passthrough` (good) vs armature-only rotation / `alignSkinnedMeshToRig` on VRM (bad).
